data.text: Andrew Duncan Glenn Roberts, commonly known as Andy Roberts, is a talented cricketer hailing from New Zealand. Born on January 31, 1980, in Auckland, Roberts is a right-arm fast-medium bowler who has represented his country in international cricket. He made his debut for New Zealand in 2003 and has since then been a vital part of the national team. With a solid bowling technique and impressive stats, Roberts has proven to be a formidable force on the field. His contributions to the sport have earned him respect and recognition among fans and players alike.
